# Route Folder Structure

Colocate route-private code under the route segment. Use `~/lib/` when **two or more route trees** import the same module.

## Route segment layout

```
{route-segment}/
  (page).tsx              # composition + wiring only
  actions.ts              # or {domain}.actions.ts when multiple action groups
  useFeature.ts           # single hook at segment root (checkout pattern)
  hooks/                  # multiple route-private hooks
  components/             # route-private UI (not __components__)
  utils/                  # route-private pure helpers
```

## Server actions

- **Colocated** in the route folder when only that segment (or its children) uses them.
  - Single group: `actions.ts` (e.g. `checkout/actions.ts`, `orders/[orderId]/actions.ts`)
  - Multiple groups in one folder: `{domain}.actions.ts` (e.g. `my-shop/shop.actions.ts`, `my-shop/storefront.actions.ts`)
- **`~/lib/{domain}/*.actions.ts`** when shared across routes (e.g. `lib/cart/cart.actions.ts`, `lib/media/media.actions.ts`, `lib/plants/plant-lifecycle.actions.ts`).
- Do not define inline `action()` in route `.tsx` files when a colocated `*.actions.ts` exists for that segment.
- Keep stable action IDs when moving actions; extend shared result types (e.g. `validationErrors`) rather than dropping error fields.

## Hooks

- Route-only hooks: `hooks/useX.ts` (or `useX.ts` at segment root if there is only one).
- Shared hooks: `~/lib/hooks/` or `~/lib/{domain}/useX.ts` when used by 2+ route trees.

## Components

- Use `components/` for route-private UI. Do **not** add new `__components__/` folders.
- Cross-route seller product UI: `products/components/shared/` (`DetailRow`, `SectionCard`, `EditableSectionCard`).
- App-wide UI stays in `~/components/`.
- Public buyer plant pages (`routes/(app)/plants/`) keep their own component tree; do not force-merge with seller product components.

## Utils

- Route-private helpers live in `utils/` (not `helpers.ts` at segment root).
- Re-export from `utils/index.ts` when a segment has multiple util modules.
- Cross-cutting helpers: `~/lib/utils/` or `~/lib/{domain}/`.

## Examples

| Concern | Location |
|---------|----------|
| Shop dashboard mutations | `my-shop/shop.actions.ts` |
| Plant overview data hook | `plants/[plantId]/hooks/usePlantOverviewData.ts` |
| Plant section save (shared) | `~/lib/plants/usePlantSectionEdit.ts` |
| Seller product section card | `products/components/shared/SectionCard.tsx` |
